(16, 1, '2012-06-20 15:49:12', '2012-06-20 15:49:12', '<h2>How Do You Use Template Tags?</h2>\r\nGoing through the various template tags in the <a title="Template Tags" href="http://codex.wordpress.org/Template_Tags">Template Tags</a> menu on the Codex, you will see that many of them are very simple, like the <tt>bloginfo()</tt> template tag, but many look very complicated to use. Let''s look at some examples of how they are used to help you understand the "language" of the template tag codes.\r\n\r\nAs we saw in the <tt>bloginfo()</tt> template tag, all it took was one word to change the output of the tag. This word is called a <em>parameter</em> and it instructs the template tag to <em>do</em> or <em>get</em> something. In this case, the instruction is to <em>get name</em> which displays the site''s name.\r\n\r\nThe template tag <tt>the_title()</tt> displays the <a title="Template Tags/the title" href="http://codex.wordpress.org/Template_Tags/the_title">title of the post</a>, usually at the top of your post article. This tag <em>gets</em> the post title and displays it, by default, but it also has a <em>do</em> in the parameters which will help you change the look and presentation of the post title.\r\n\r\nBy default, the tag looks like this:', 'How Do You Use Template Tags', 'As we saw in the bloginfo() template tag, all it took was one word to change the output of the tag.', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'how-do-you-use-template-tags', '', '', '2012-06-20 15:49:12', '2012-06-20 15:49:12', '', 0, 'http://localhost/~rajankz/newaast/?p=16', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(17, 1, '2012-06-20 15:49:03', '2012-06-20 15:49:03', '<h2>How Do You Use Template Tags?</h2>\nGoing through the various template tags in the <a title="Template Tags" href="http://codex.wordpress.org/Template_Tags">Template Tags</a> menu on the Codex, you will see that many of them are very simple, like the <tt>bloginfo()</tt> template tag, but many look very complicated to use. Let''s look at some examples of how they are used to help you understand the "language" of the template tag codes.\n\nAs we saw in the <tt>bloginfo()</tt> template tag, all it took was one word to change the output of the tag. This word is called a <em>parameter</em> and it instructs the template tag to <em>do</em> or <em>get</em> something. In this case, the instruction is to <em>get name</em> which displays the site''s name.\n\nThe template tag <tt>the_title()</tt> displays the <a title="Template Tags/the title" href="http://codex.wordpress.org/Template_Tags/the_title">title of the post</a>, usually at the top of your post article. This tag <em>gets</em> the post title and displays it, by default, but it also has a <em>do</em> in the parameters which will help you change the look and presentation of the post title.\n\nBy default, the tag looks like this:', 'How Do You Use Template Tags', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '16-revision', '', '', '2012-06-20 15:49:03', '2012-06-20 15:49:03', '', 16, 'http://localhost/~rajankz/newaast/2012/06/20/16-revision/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(18, 1, '2012-06-20 18:55:06', '2012-06-20 18:55:06', 'The Asian American Studies Program (AAST) at the University of Maryland is one of the premier ethnic studies programs in the United States focusing on the identities and experiences of Asian Americans.\r\n\r\nOur program is uniquely positioned as an important venue for scholarship in Asian American ethnic studies with its close proximity to Washington, D.C., the fourth largest concentration of Asian Americans in the nation. Asian Americans are the largest ethnic minority group on campus, comprising 15 percent of the undergraduate student body. With nearly 500 students enrolled in our courses each semester and more than 60 students in our minor program, our curriculum is filling an important academic niche and serving the needs of our campus.\r\n\r\nAAST is striving to build a program as diverse as our community.', 'About Us', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'open', '', 'about-us', '', '', '2012-06-22 17:29:06', '2012-06-22 17:29:06', '', 0, 'http://localhost/~rajankz/newaast/?page_id=18', 0, 'page', '', 0),
